reviewText: The usual competence of the Great Courses provides an excellent intro to nano for the general reader. A very gentle intro to the physics, biochemistry, medical and industrial applications as it stood in 2012.  Took away one star as its getting slightly dated but should still be ok until 2020 or so.
More like a presentation to potential investors -- which is a bit off putting --  but you do learn
Way too revealing for the INNOCENCE of First Holy Communion. This does not feel appropriate for little girls who should be exemplifying purity and holiness.
